    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"practical assumption\" feels like such a cop out. if it's all just noise and projections, then all this effort to \"connect\" or \"live life\" feels completely pointless. if i'm the only one actually here, and everything else is just these hallucinations causing me pain... does that make the struggle worth it? or is the struggle just part of the illusion?",
